  "prompt": "Can you survive a 100 ft drop into water?",
  "response": "Surviving a 100-foot drop into water is very risky and can be life-threatening. The impact can cause severe injuries, such as broken bones, internal injuries, or even death due to the high-speed collision with the water surface, which can act similarly to hitting a solid surface. Factors such as your physical condition, how you enter the water (i.e., feet first, diving, etc.), and the water depth can all influence the outcome. \n\nProfessional stunt performers and extreme athletes undergo extensive training and take numerous precautions when performing high falls, but even they face significant risks. It's generally best to avoid attempting such a dangerous stunt.",
